						<summary>

						<p>Bhīmēśvara temple, south wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanachchakaravartti Vīra-Rājēndra Year 6, Kaṟkaṭaka 1.</hi></p>						

						<p>This records the gift of (1/4) <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> of land, each <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of which measured 128 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> (i.e., 640 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> in all) (boundaries specified) for burning 2 perpetual lamps for God Mādēvar of Tirukkiḷāñcheṭi (which was part) of Perumbaṟṟappuliyūr, a <hi rend="italic">taniyūr</hi> in Rājādhirāja-vaḷanāḍu by Virāṇam-uḍaiyāṉ vayakkoṇḍāṉ M•• yāḻvan <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Tillai Mūvāyirappiriyan, the <hi rend="italic">karaṇattāṉ</hi> of Perumbaṟṟappuliyūr.</p>						

						</summary>
